{{page-title "Gutters Helpers"}}

<h2 class="dummy-h2">Gutters helpers</h2>

<section>
  <h3 class="dummy-h3" id="overview">
    <a href="#overview" class="dummy-link-section">§</a>
    Overview
  </h3>

  <p class="dummy-paragraph">
    Gutters CSS helper classes can be used to add consistent vertical or horizontal “gutter” spacing between child
    elements.
  </p>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">
    (Similar to
    <a href="https://every-layout.dev/layouts/stack/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“The Stack” pattern from
      “Every Layout”</a>
    and
    <a href="/components/button-set/">"Hds::ButtonSet"</a>.)
  </p>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">
    Using Gutters CSS helper classes gives you flexibility in applying spacing styles to the elements of your choice so
    that you can choose more appropriate semantic elements. However, "Gutters" is also available as the
    <a href="/components/gutters/">“Hds::Gutters” Ember component</a>
    if you prefer.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="dummy-paragraph">
  <h3 class="dummy-h3" id="how-to-use"><a href="#how-to-use" class="dummy-link-section">§</a> How to use</h3>

  <p>
    <strong>Add the CSS helper classes to a parent element or component to set spacing between nested child elements.</strong>
  </p>

  <h4 class="dummy-h4" id="helper-gutters-primary-classes">Primary CSS helper classes</h4>
  <dl class="dummy-component-props" aria-labelledby="helper-gutters-primary-classes">
    <dt>.hds-gutters-horizontal</dt>
    <dd>Set vertical gutter spacing between child elements. Uses a default spacing size of “md”.</dd>

    <dt>.hds-gutters-vertical</dt>
    <dd>Set horizontal gutter spacing between child elements. Uses a default spacing size of “md”.</dd>
  </dl>

  <h4 class="dummy-h4" id="helper-gutters-modifier-classes">CSS modifier classes</h4>
  <p>Use the modifier classes in addition to the primary classes to override the default spacing size.</p>
  <dl class="dummy-component-props" aria-labelledby="helper-gutters-modifier-classes">
    <dt>.hds-gutters-spacing-xxs</dt>
    <dd>Override the default spacing size to use “xxs” size instead.</dd>

    <dt>.hds-gutters-spacing-xs</dt>
    <dd>Override the default spacing size to use “xs” size instead.</dd>

    <dt>.hds-gutters-spacing-sm</dt>
    <dd>Override the default spacing size to use “sm” size instead.</dd>

    <dt>.hds-gutters-spacing-md</dt>
    <dd>The default spacing size is “md” so you should not need to add this modifier. It is included for completeness.</dd>

    <dt>.hds-gutters-spacing-lg</dt>
    <dd>Override the default spacing size to use “lg” size instead.</dd>

    <dt>.hds-gutters-spacing-xl</dt>
    <dd>Override the default spacing size to use “xl” size instead.</dd>

    <dt>.hds-gutters-spacing-xxl</dt>
    <dd>Override the default spacing size to use “xxl” size instead.</dd>
  </dl>

  <h4 class="dummy-h4" id="helper-gutters-custom-spacing">CSS custom property</h4>
  <p>If none of the preset spacing sizes meet your needs, you may use an inline style to set a custom spacing size.</p>
  <dl class="dummy-component-props" aria-labelledby="helper-gutters-custom-spacing">
    <dt>--hds-spacing</dt>
    <dd>
      <p>
        Use this CSS custom property within an HTML style attribute to set a custom spacing size using any valid CSS
        unit. Negative values are not supported.
      </p>
    </dd>
  </dl>

  <h4 class="dummy-h4" id="helper-gutters-spacing-scale">Preset spacing scale:</h4>
  <p>
    The spacing scale values map to a
    <a
      href="https://www.figma.com/file/oQsMzMMnynfPWpMEt91OpH/HDS-Product---Foundations?node-id=2008%3A3"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
    >
      loose spacing scale in HDS
    </a>. Abbreviations are based on English words vs. numbers for ease in quick comprehension and visualization.
    Abbrevations use all letters instead of a mix of letters and numbers both for consistency and to adhere to variable
    naming practices which forbid starting variables names with a number (This is not actually true for CSS custom
    property but it is true for JavaScript variables for instance).
  </p>
  <dl class="dummy-component-props" aria-labelledby="helper-gutters-spacing-scale">
    <dt>xxs</dt>
    <dd><p>An abbreviation for “eXtra eXtra Small”.</p></dd>

    <dt>xs</dt>
    <dd><p>An abbreviation for “eXtra Small”.</p></dd>

    <dt>sm</dt>
    <dd><p>An abbreviation for “SMall”.</p></dd>

    <dt>md</dt>
    <dd><p>An abbreviation for “MeDium”. This is the default “Gutters” spacing size.</p></dd>

    <dt>lg</dt>
    <dd><p>An abbreviation for “LarGe”.</p></dd>

    <dt>xl</dt>
    <dd><p>An abbreviation for “eXtra LarGe”.</p></dd>

    <dt>xxl</dt>
    <dd><p>An abbreviation for “eXtra eXtra LarGe”.</p></dd>
  </dl>

  <h4 class="dummy-h4">Example code</h4>
  <h5 class="dummy-h5">Set vertical spacing between elements</h5>
  <h6 class="dummy-h6">Using default “md” vertical spacing:</h6>
  {{! prettier-ignore-start }}
  <CodeBlock
    @language="markup"
    @code='
      <ul class="hds-gutters-vertical">
        <li>item 1</li>
        <li>item 2</li>
        <li>item 3</li>
      </ul>
    '
  />
  {{! prettier-ignore-end }}

  <h6 class="dummy-h6">Using “lg” spacing size from the preset scale:</h6>
  {{! prettier-ignore-start }}
  <CodeBlock
    @language="markup"
    @code='
      <ul class="hds-gutters-vertical hds-gutters-spacing-lg">
        <li>item 1</li>
        <li>item 2</li>
        <li>item 3</li>
      </ul>
    '
  />
  {{! prettier-ignore-end }}

  <h6 class="dummy-h6">Using a custom spacing size:</h6>
  {{! prettier-ignore-start }}
  <CodeBlock
    @language="markup"
    @code='
      <ul class="hds-gutters-vertical" style="--hds-spacing: 2.5rem">
        <li>item 1</li>
        <li>item 2</li>
        <li>item 3</li>
      </ul>
    '
  />
  {{! prettier-ignore-end }}

  <h5 class="dummy-h5">Set horizontal spacing between elements</h5>
  <h6 class="dummy-h6">Using default “md” horizontal spacing:</h6>
  {{! prettier-ignore-start }}
  <CodeBlock
    @language="markup"
    @code='
      <p class="hds-gutters-horizontal">
        <span>Child 1</span>
        <span>Child 2</span>
        <span>Child 3</span>
      </p>
    '
  />
  {{! prettier-ignore-end }}
</section>

